# Thriden component versions — the pinned umbrella combination.
#
# NON-SECRET, git-shipped. This is the machine-readable source of truth for
# which image tags a host runs. It is bumped in the SAME change that cuts each
# `thriden-v*` umbrella (see docs/versioning.md § Release procedure), so a plain
# `git pull` carries the target versions to every host with no SOPS decrypt
# needed to read or set them. That is what lets `bin/thriden-upgrade.sh` be a
# single advertised command ().
#
# Loaded by the deploy commands (thriden-upgrade.sh, thriden-scion-up.sh,
# thriden-redeploy.sh) and exported into the env, so `docker compose`
# interpolation resolves them. A *_VERSION line still present in a host's
# encrypted stack.enc.env (the legacy pre-tpo4 model) takes precedence until
# removed — see docs/runbook-upgrade-thriden.md § Migrating off stack.enc.env
# version pins. compose.prod.yml carries the substrate values as `:-` backstops.

# Substrate (forge-web, nooscope):
FORGE_VERSION=v0.7.0
NOOSCOPE_VERSION=v0.3.0

# Per-Scion drop-ins (engram-<short> brain, forge-<short> runtime):
ENGRAM_VERSION=v0.2.8
FORGE_RUNTIME_VERSION=v0.7.0
